Thermal Noise Simulation and Examination
Objective

This project aims to model and study thermal noise using MATLAB. The characteristics of thermal noise are demonstrated in both the time domain and the frequency domain through Power Spectral Density (PSD) analysis.

Prerequisites

MATLAB

Signal Processing Toolbox (required for the pwelch function)

How to Use

Clone or download the repository to your local system.

Open the main MATLAB script (for example, thermal_noise.m).

Run the script to execute the simulation and display the generated plots.

Default System Parameters

Bandwidth (B): 1 MHz

Resistance (R): 100 ohms

Temperature (T): 300 K

Boltzmann Constant (k):

