showing the dependence of thermal noise on physical parameters.

PSD Analysis:
The power spectral density remains flat across the frequency range, confirming that thermal noise power is uniformly distributed over bandwidth.

Effect of Parameter Variation:

Bandwidth: Changing the bandwidth modifies the overall noise variance in the time domain while keeping the PSD level unchanged.

Resistance and Temperature: Increasing either resistance or temperature increases both the time-domain noise amplitude and the constant power level observed in the PSD plot.
